<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

								The Reward Based Eating Drive (RED) Scale (13 item scale)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 09-26-2023
last updated:  09-26-2023 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 09-26-2023 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements Millisecond's computerized version of The Reward Based Eating Drive (RED) Scale (13 item scale)

survey downloaded from:
https://www.sealab.ucsf.edu/red-scale

Reference:
Mason, A.E., Vainik, U., Acree, M., Tomiyama, A.J., Dagher, A., Epel, E.S., & Hecht F.M. (2017). Improving assessment of the spectrum of 
reward-related eating: The RED-13. Frontiers in Psychology, May 30;8:795.
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

self-report measure consisting of 13 5-point Likert Scale questions
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 2 minutes to complete

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'red.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								Scale: 0 (Strongly Disagree) - 4 (Strongly Agree)
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'red_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)	
							
RED_13_total:				sum of all individual scores (Range: 0-52)	, rated on scale 0 (Strongly Disagree) - 4 (Strongly Agree)

+ all individual responses						

</usermanual>

**************************************************************************************************************
				!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.6.1.0 or higher

<defaults>
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/minimumversion = "6.6.1.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
</defaults>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: data file explanations under User Manual Information at the top

***********************
raw data file
***********************

***********************
summary data file
***********************
<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed,

expressions.RED_13_total,

//////raw data:
radioButtons.q1.response,
radioButtons.q2.response,
radioButtons.q3.response,
radioButtons.q4.response,
radioButtons.q5.response,
radioButtons.q6.response,
radioButtons.q7.response,
radioButtons.q8.response,
radioButtons.q9.response,
radioButtons.q10.response,
radioButtons.q11.response,
radioButtons.q12.response,
radioButtons.q13.response


)
</summarydata>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<expressions>
/RED_13_total = return (radioButtons.q1.response + radioButtons.q2.response + radioButtons.q3.response + radioButtons.q4.response +
radioButtons.q5.response + radioButtons.q6.response + radioButtons.q7.response + radioButtons.q8.response +
radioButtons.q9.response + radioButtons.q10.response + radioButtons.q11.response + radioButtons.q12.response + radioButtons.q13.response)
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "1. I feel out of control in the presence of delicious food"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2>
/caption = "2. When I start eating, I just can’t seem to stop"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3>
/caption = "3. It is difficult for me to leave food on my plate"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4>
/caption = "4. When it comes to foods I love, I have no willpower"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5>
/caption = "5. I get so hungry that my stomach often seems like a bottomless pit"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6>
/caption = "6. I don’t get full easily"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7>
/caption = "7. It seems like most of my waking hours are preoccupied by thoughts about eating or not eating"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8>
/caption = "8. I have days when I can’t seem to think about anything else but food"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9>
/caption = "9. Food is always on my mind"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10>
/caption = "10. I feel hungry all the time"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q11>
/caption = "11. I can’t stop thinking about eating no matter how hard I try"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q12>
/caption = "12. I find myself continuing to consume certain foods even though I am no longer hungry"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q13>
/caption = "13. If food tastes good to me, I eat more than usual"
/ options = ("Strongly<br>Disagree", "Disagree", "Neither Agree<br>nor Disagree", "Agree", "Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionvalues = ("0", "1", "2", "3", "4")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage RED_1>
/ caption = "Please read every question and indicate how much you agree or disagree.<br>"
/ subcaption = ""
/questions = [1 = q1, q2, q3]
</surveypage>

<surveypage RED_2>
/ caption = "Please read every question and indicate how much you agree or disagree.<br>"
/ subcaption = ""
/questions = [1 = q4, q5, q6]
</surveypage>

<surveypage RED_3>
/ caption = "Please read every question and indicate how much you agree or disagree.<br>"
/ subcaption = ""
/questions = [1 = q7, q8, q9]
</surveypage>

<surveypage RED_4>
/ caption = "Please read every question and indicate how much you agree or disagree.<br>"
/ subcaption = ""
/questions = [1 = q10, q11, q12,]
</surveypage>

<surveypage RED_5>
/ caption = "Please read every question and indicate how much you agree or disagree.<br>"
/ subcaption = ""
/questions = [1 = q13]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
- presents the surveypages

<survey RED>
/pages = [
	1 = RED_1;
	2 = RED_2;
	3 = RED_3;	
	4 = RED_4;
	5 = RED_5;	
]
/screencapture = false
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = false
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ finishlabel = "Finish"
</survey>

*******************************************************************************************************************
												End of File
